#Text=Roger Mason ( musician )
#Text=For other people with the same name , see Roger Mason .
#Text=Roger Ashley Mason is an Australian keyboardist who has been a member of new wave groups Models , Absent Friends and Icehouse .
#Text=He was a session and backing musician for United Kingdom 's Gary Numan and for various Australian artists .
#Text=From the early 1990s he has composed music for television and feature films .

#Text=He appeared on Models best performed album , Out of Mind , Out of Sight ( 1985 ) which reached No.3 on the Australian Kent Music Report Albums Chart and spawned a No.2 hit " Barbados " and a No.1 hit " Out of Mind , Out of Sight " .
#Text=On 27 October 2010 , Models were inducted into the ARIA Hall of Fame by former member , Wendy Matthews .

#Text=As a composer , he has won Australasian Performing Right Association ( APRA ) Awards for his work on The Extra ( 2005 ) , Peking to Paris ( 2006 ) , The Last Confession of Alexander Pearce ( 2009 ) .
#Text=Biography
#Text=Early years
#Text=Roger Ashley Mason [ 1 ] [ 2 ] was a keyboardist in Colt early in 1979 .

#Text=He joined vocalist and guitarist James Freud ( ex-Spread , Teenage Radio Stars ) in James Freud & the Radio Stars with fellow Colt members Murray Doherty on bass guitar , Glenn McGrath on drums and Bryan Thomas on guitar , and later Tony Harvey on guitar and Mick Prague on bass .

#Text=This line up plus various guest artists recorded the album " Breaking Silence " between July and November 1979 with further contributions made by Tony Lugton and Peter Cook before its completion and release in 1980 . [ 3 ] [ 4 ]
#Text=Further changes by year 's end resulted in Freud and Mason joined by Peter Cook on guitar and backing vocals and Tommy Hosie on drums . [ 3 ]
#Text=They signed with Mushroom Records and their debut single , " Modern Girl , " was released in May 1980 , which peaked at No.12 on the Australian Kent Music Report Singles Chart . [ 3 ] [ 5 ]
#Text=They supported the English singer-keyboardist , Gary Numan , on his Australian tour .
#Text=James Freud & the Radio Stars ' debut album Breaking Silence was released in June , it was produced by Tony Cohen . [ 3 ] [ 4 ]
#Text=Numan liked the album and offered to produce the next one in London , as there was already a UK band called The Radio Stars , a name change to James Freud & Berlin occurred .
#Text=While in London , Mason joined Numan 's backing band and was recorded on the live album , Living Ornaments ' 80 . [ 6 ]
#Text=Neither Freud nor Numan were happy with the London-recorded album for James Freud & Berlin and it was not released and one month later , in March 1981 , Freud disbanded the group . [ 7 ]
#Text=Freud and Mason returned to the UK with the intention of forming a new band , Orient-R , which only played a single performance before disbanding .
#Text=Mason then went on to join Numan 's touring band , and appeared on Numan 's 1981 album , Dance and subsequent 1982 album , I , Assassin .
#Text=While in London , Mason worked for glam rock guitarist , Rob Dean ( ex- Japan , Numan 's touring band ) on a potential solo album .
#Text=By 1984 , Mason and Dean had combined with Hugo Burnham ( Gang of Four ) and Australian singer and bass guitarist Philip Foxman ( Supernaut ) to form funk rock outfit , Illustrated Man . [ 4 ]
#Text=They released a six-track mini-LP , Illustrated Man , then toured to New York but soon disbanded .
#Text=Models
#Text=In late 1984 , Mason re-joined with Freud to replace Andrew Duffield on keyboards in Models . [ 7 ]

#Text=He appeared on their best performed album , Out of Mind , Out of Sight which reached No.3 on the Australian Kent Music Report Albums Chart and spawned a No.2 hit " Barbados " and a No.1 hit " Out of Mind , Out of Sight " . [ 5 ]

#Text=With Mason and Freud , the line-up of Models was Sean Kelly on lead guitar and vocals , Canadian-born Wendy Matthews on backing vocals , New Zealand-born Barton Price on drums and James Valentine on saxophone .
#Text=Their final studio album , Models ' Media was released in December 1986 , which peaked in the Top30 and the band had a slot on the Australian Made Tour into early 1987 . [ 7 ]
#Text=Mason as lead singer and Kelly , formed a side-project , The Clampetts , to record cover versions of nine country music tracks , which was released in 1987 as The Last Hoedown . [ 4 ] [ 8 ]
#Text=Later projects
#Text=Mason joined Jenny Morris 's backing band late in 1987 , together with Amanda Vincent ( ex- Eurogliders ) , Jehan Lindsay ( Richard Clapton Band ) , Paul Burton ( Mark Williams Band )
#Text=following the release of Morris ' debut solo album , Body and Soul .
#Text=In 1988 Mason toured with Los Angeles new wave group Wall of Voodoo and appeared on their live album The Ugly Americans in Australia .
#Text=In late 1989 Mason re-united with former Models members , Kelly and Matthews performing on Absent Friends ' first single , " Hallelujah " .
#Text=Mason then toured with Icehouse , following the release of their seventh studio album , Code Blue .
#Text=He also was a member of Tommy Emmanuel 's touring band between 1988 and 1992 . [ 4 ]

#Text=In 1990 , Matthews recorded her debut solo album migr with the assistance of Mason and various band mates , Garry Gary Beers ( Absent Friends , INXS ) , Kelly , Mick King ( Absent Friends ) , Valentine and Duffield as well as Tim Finn and Peter Blakeley . [ 9 ]
#Text=Mason wrote her hit song , " Token Angels " which reached No.18 on the Australian singles chart and won Matthews an ARIA Award in 1991 for ' Breakthrough Artist  Single ' . [ 10 ] [ 11 ]

column1: #Text=1992 saw Mason ( keyboards ) join Johnny Diesel 's ' Rock ' n ' Soul ' Tour , with Kane Baker on drums , Leslie Barlow on backing vocals , Matthew Branton on guitar and Jim Hilbun on bass guitar . [ 12 ]
#Text=In 1997 , Mason teamed up with Graeme Revell to create the album Vision II - Spirit of Rumi , released through New York based Angel Records .
#Text=The two coproduced , supplied some of the instrumental accompaniment , and set to music 11 poems by renowned 13th century poet Jall ad-Dn Muhammad Rm .
#Text=Vocals were provided by Noa , Lori Garson , Esther Dobong'Na Essiene a.k.a. Estha Divine , and the late Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan [ 13 ] .
#Text=As a composer , Mason has won Australasian Performing Right Association ( APRA ) Awards for ' Best Soundtrack Album ' for The Extra in 2005 , [ 14 ]
#Text=' Best Music for a Television Series or Serial ' for Peking to Paris in 2006 , [ 15 ] ' Best Music for a Telemovie ' for The Last Confession of Alexander Pearce
#Text=in 2009 , and Australian Academy of Cinema and Television Arts ( AACTA ) Awards for ' Best Original Music Score in Television ' for The Code ( Episode 1 ) ( ABC ) in 2015 . [ 16 ] [ 17 ]
#Text=On 27 October 2010 , Models were inducted into the ARIA Hall of Fame by Matthews . [ 18 ] [ 19 ]
